following is the most appropriate course of action regarding recommending the weight loss drug?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Delegate weight loss drug recommendations to clinic staff members","Recommend the weight loss drug without disclosing the shareholding","Only recommend alternative weight loss medications","Avoid recommending any weight loss drugs due to the shareholding","Disclose the shareholding when recommending the weight loss drug"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edisclose the shareholding when recommending the weight loss drug\u003C/strong\u003E. Medical practitioners have an ethical obligation to be transparent about any potential conflicts of interest that could influence their clinical recommendations. This allows patients to make informed decisions about their care with full knowledge of potential conflicts of interest.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelegate weight loss drug recommendations to clinic staff members\u003C/strong\u003E - This does not remove the obligation to disclose the shareholding and may be seen as attempting to obscure the conflict of interest\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecommend the weight loss drug without disclosing the shareholding\u003C/strong\u003E - This lacks transparency and violates ethical guidelines requiring disclosure of potential conflicts of interest\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOnly recommend alternative weight loss medications\u003C/strong\u003E - Avoiding products solely due to shareholding may deny patients access to beneficial treatments, when disclosure would be more appropriate\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAvoid recommending any weight loss drugs due to the shareholding\u003C/strong\u003E - Having shares in a pharmaceutical company does not preclude recommending appropriate medications, provided there is full disclosure\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMedical practitioners must maintain professional integrity by being open about potential conflicts of interest while ensuring clinical recommendations are based on patient needs rather than personal gain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn the Code of Conduct, Good Medical Practice involves: \u0027Not allowing any financial or commercial interest in a hospital, other healthcare organisation, or company providing or manufacturing healthcare services or products to adversely affect the way you treat patients. When you or your immediate family have such an interest and that interest could be perceived to influence the care you provide, you must inform your patient.\u0027 (10.12.9)\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Medical practitioners must declare any financial interests that could influence patient care decisions.","Recommending products in which practitioners have a financial interest requires full disclosure to patients.","Medical practitioners must avoid exploiting the doctor-patient relationship for financial gain."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"87050"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18831"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"87050","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/87050"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-03T20:53:11+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-03T20:55:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11564"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"